    "Crucial to alignment is the ability of these models to adapt based on feedback, minimize biases, and respect user autonomy and privacy (Gabriel, 2020; Liao, 2020; Wang et al., 2023).",
    "Studies have shown evidence for stigma against people with dementia on the media platform X, formerly known as Twitter (Oscar et al., 2017; Bacsu et al., 2022), and in the wider social media landscape (Nguyen and Li, 2020).",
    "Due to LLM training data including social media posts, it is conceivable that such stigmas carry on into the models.",
    "Datasets such as BOLD (Dhamala et al., 2021) provide prompts and metrics for assessing such biases.",
    "Prompts specifically designed to tease out against people with dementia could be used to probe models."
